0.label: Universal colors
0.notes: These colors apply to most characters in the show. Use these unless a different color is specified. Eye Shines: Use for eye reflections, sclera and teeth. Eye Pupil: Use for eye pupil, eyelashes, eye outlines and on eyelids (for emotional turmoil at ~5-15% opacity)

118.label: Princess Ember
118.notes:
For bottom stroke on wings use Outline Bottom Gradient (only apply gradient to wing "spokes").
Diamond-like scale coloring is inconsistent between some shots but there's up to four different colors in use, darkening near tail.

132.label: King Sombra
132.notes:
Far legs use darker colors.
Sombra has a lot of gradients with repeating colors. You can simplify this by using the same gradients in different parts with some tweaking of the size and stop placement.
The magic "bubbles" are fading gradients that vary according to the animation frame which makes colour picking them nigh impossible, especially amid the compression.
The eye smoke is a fading gradient whose color differs in different scenes. This is just a best guess for it.
The armor sections are numbered going down the neck i.e. Section 1 is the uppermost one.

119.label: Tank
119.notes:
Far Legs use darker colors.
In some scenes, Tank uses an alternate set of colors for the tongue.
For accurate goggle lenses: Group together the Fill (100% Normal blending) and the Highlights (75% Color Dodge blending) and set the group to 50% opacity.
For a less accurate version, group together the Fill and the Highlights (both 100% opacity, Normal blending) and set the group to 50% opacity.
